Liverpool travel to play Chelsea in the Premier League this season, having won their opening five fixtures so far. The Reds are five points clear at the top of the table, ahead of rivals Manchester City. It has been a stop-start campaign for Frank Lampard at Stamford Bridge, but they currently sit sixth on the table and will be looking to climb up. Kick off is 4.30pm West African time. Chelsea XI vs Liverpool: Kepa, Azpilicueta, Christensen, Tomori, Emerson, Kante, Jorginho, Kovacic, Willian, Mount, Abraham Liverpool XI vs Chelsea: Adrian, Alexander-Arnold, Matip, Van Dijk, Robertson, Fabinho, Wijnaldum, Henderson, Mane, Salah, Firmino Sunday, September 22
